1 0 0 1 50 732 Tm (Why Precision Matters) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 718 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 704 Tm (The same equations run under different number systems depending on weight_dtype.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 690 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 676 Tm (float16 uses less memory, but values can overflow, underflow, or lose detail. This can ) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 662 Tm (corrupt attention scores, noise predictions, scheduler updates, or VAE decoding.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 648 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 634 Tm (float32 uses more memory, but gives the equations more numeric room. That is why float32) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 620 Tm ( is often more stable and why float16 can sometimes produce a black image.) Tj
